  <div class="editable-message-body">
    <div class="comment-text editable-message-text" itemprop="commentText"><p>I was contacted by folks from Mirantis. They found out that:</p>
<p>1. This feature is not directly tied to auto-provisioning<br />
2. There are mappings that don&#x27;t use auto-provisioning and are still vulnerable to issue with incorrect roles being assigned.</p>
<p>I believe that their issue and mine are actually the same issue. My patch still fixes the bug, but now the affected versions are Mitaka, Newton and Ocata.</p>
<p>For example, people with mapping like <a rel="nofollow" href="http://paste.openstack.org/show/606171/">http://<wbr />paste.openstack<wbr />.org/show/<wbr />606171/</a> are affected too.<br />
As far as i understand, all installations with mappings not using key &quot;groups&quot; are affected.</p>
<p>I suggest to add the person who reported the issue to me to this bugreport. His profile at lp is <a rel="nofollow" href="https://launchpad.net/~dmitrymex">https:/<wbr />/launchpad.<wbr />net/~dmitrymex</a></p></div>
    
    
    
  </div>

  <div class="editable-message-form" style="display: none">
     <textarea style="width: 100%" rows="10">I was contacted by folks from Mirantis. They found out that:

1. This feature is not directly tied to auto-provisioning
2. There are mappings that don't use auto-provisioning and are still vulnerable to issue with incorrect roles being assigned.

I believe that their issue and mine are actually the same issue. My patch still fixes the bug, but now the affected versions are Mitaka, Newton and Ocata.

For example, people with mapping like http://paste.openstack.org/show/606171/ are affected too.
As far as i understand, all installations with mappings not using key "groups" are affected.

I suggest to add the person who reported the issue to me to this bugreport. His profile at lp is https://launchpad.net/~dmitrymex</textarea>
